      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It is a significant change to take a sudden break from warfarin, as your medication dosage must be managed carefully by your doctor rather than adjusted based on how you feel. Stopping or drastically reducing your dose without medical supervision could cause your blood clotting times to drop, increasing the risk of serious heart clots. You should definitely contact your cardiology team before making any changes to your routine to ensure your INR stays within the safe target range.",
