      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Exercise alone does not naturally thin the blood enough to safely reduce warfarin dosage, as warfarin's effectiveness depends on specific INR levels rather than just physical activity. Even with a \"clean\" diet, small fluctuations in food sources or metabolism can disrupt a dose of 2mg, making it unpredictable and potentially dangerous to self-adjust. Please discuss these concerns with your doctor so they can assess your INR before ever changing your current 5mg routine.",
